Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @breadcrumbs{50%grams}, @black sesame seeds{5%grams} and @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} into another medium bowl and season with the @salt{1/4%tsp} and pepper.

Season the @British chicken thighs{4}, then dip them into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring they're completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden-brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a large baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{8-11%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.

In a medium bowl, mix together the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}, squeeze of lime, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, half the lime zest and a third of the @mayonnaise{96%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set your slaw aside for later.

Once the oil has cooled, wipe out the chicken pan. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @vegetable gyozas{1%pack} and fry until golden on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}. Reduce the heat to medium-low, add @water{1%tbsp} to the pan and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until the gyozas are piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Add the @teriyaki sauce{50%grams} to the pan and turn the gyozas to glaze them. Add a squeeze of lime juice.

When everything's ready, share your fried chicken between your plates and serve with your chips and coleslaw alongside. Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over and a dollop of the remaining mayonnaise.

On a separate #side plate{}, serve your teriyaki gyozas and scatter over the spring onion to finish. Enjoy!